title: Lanús Partido
text:
Lanús is a <a href="Partidos%20of%20Buenos%20Aires">partido</a> in <a href="Buenos%20Aires%20Province">Buenos Aires Province</a>, <a href="Argentina">Argentina</a>, at the south of the <a href="Gran%20Buenos%20Aires">Gran Buenos Aires</a> urban conglomerate neighbouring <a href="Buenos%20Aires">Buenos Aires</a> city.
The partido has an area of , and a population of 453,500 (). Its capital is the city of <a href="Lan%C3%BAs">Lanús</a>.
Lanús Partido is connected to the Buenos Aires city across the <a href="Puente%20Valent%C3%ADn%20Alsina">Valentín Alsina Bridge</a> over the <a href="Riachuelo%20River">Riachuelo River</a>. The name of the partido comes from the former land owner <a href="Anacarsis%20Lan%C3%BAs">Anacarsis Lanús</a>, who was a pioneer in the urbanization of the area.
Sports.
The partido is home to <a href="Club%20Atl%C3%A9tico%20Lan%C3%BAs">Club Atlético Lanús</a>, a <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> club playing in the <a href="Primera%20Division%20Argentina">Argentine Primera Division</a>.
